# Day 8 - Lightning Web Components (LWC)

## 1. What is LWC?

Lightning Web Components (LWC) is a modern UI framework used in Salesforce to build fast and reusable user interfaces.

LWC uses:
- HTML
- JavaScript
- CSS
- Metadata configuration

It helps developers create interactive and reusable components for Salesforce applications.

---

## 2. Why Salesforce Uses LWC

Salesforce uses LWC because it:
- Improves performance
- Supports reusable UI components
- Uses modern web standards
- Makes development faster and modular
- Provides better user experience

LWC helps developers build scalable enterprise applications.

